sentences: Howard Earl Bailey Jr. (born March 9, 1980), known professionally as Chingy, is an American rapper, record producer and actor.
He toured as an opening act with Nelly in the summer of 2002 and then became a protégé of Ludacris, who signed him to his newly formed Disturbing Tha Peace (DTP) record label.
Chingy's 2003 debut album, Jackpot, sold two million copies, thanks to the boost from "Right Thurr".

A second album, Powerballin', was released in 2004 to mixed reviews, and his 2006 release Hoodstar spawned the hit singles "Pullin' Me Back" (featuring Tyrese Gibson) and "Dem Jeans" (featuring Jermaine Dupri).
